participating-org.narrative:
STICHTING Internet Now! Foundation abbreviated as SINF has its seat in the City of The Hague, incorporated on 11 July 2012 to perform the following objectives;
# To establish or cause to be established internet access points, together with the associated infrastructure, for the benefit of local communities in Africa;
# To provide or cause to e provided reliable, affordable and sustainable internet access to local residents, and to local farmers in particular;
# To facilitate or cause to be facilitatedthe outsourcing of work to local people;
# To provide local farmers or cause local farmers to be provided with access to a commodities trading platform;
# To establish or cause to be established one or more companies of any legal form (under foreign law) designed to establish and facilitate internet access points;
# To participate in or hold shares in the capital  of such companies;
# To provide facilities and assistance to such companies in any way whatsoever.

The role of SINF on the internet Nowproject include among others the following;
# SINF is the principal shareholder of SINFA Uganda limited, the social enterprise that runs the operations for the services and infrastructure that the Internet Now project sets up.
# SINF also acts as the conduit via which working capital is injected into SINFA Uganda by Internet Now.
